{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Fz2U8gSiuyYTguzR52G4vn","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Verification Proof: 16-5-rewrite-harness-run-verification-dispatch\n     2→\n     3→**Tier:** test-provable\n     4→**Story:** 16-5-rewrite-harness-run-verification-dispatch\n     5→**Date:** 2026-03-27\n     6→**Verifier:** Claude Opus 4.6 (1M context)\n     7→\n     8→## Build & Test Results\n     9→\n    10→| Check | Result | Details |\n    11→|-------|--------|---------|\n    12→| Build (`npm run build`) | PASS | tsup compiled successfully, 0 errors |\n    13→| BATS Tests (`npm test`) | PASS | 321 total, 316 passed, 5 failed (unrelated `all_tasks_complete` tests) |\n    14→| Unit Tests (`vitest run`) | PASS | 34/34 dispatch-specific tests passed |\n    15→| Lint (`npm run lint`) | PASS | 0 errors, 47 warnings (none in story-related files) |\n    16→| Coverage (`vitest --coverage`) | PASS | 97.45% statements overall, 97.46% in verify module |\n    17→\n    18→## Acceptance Criteria Verification\n    19→\n    20→### AC1: Step 3d-0 derives tier from AC-level tags using maxTier()\n    21→**Result:** PASS\n    22→\n    23→**Evidence:**\n    24→- Line 269: `Step 3d-0: Read the story file and derive the verification tier from AC-level tags.`\n    25→- Line 273: `Ignore the story-level <!-- verification-tier: ... --> tag (if present). It is NOT used for dispatch. AC-level tags are the sole source of truth.`\n    26→- Line 275: `Parse ALL lines in the Acceptance Criteria section. For each AC, extract its <!-- verification: {tier} --> tag`\n    27→- Line 277: `Compute the story's derived tier: maxTier(collectedTiers). If no AC-level tags are found at all, default to test-provable.`\n    28→- 4/4 unit tests pass for AC1 group\n    29→\n    30→### AC2: test-provable dispatches build+test subagent, no Docker\n    31→**Result:** PASS\n    32→\n    33→**Evidence:**\n    34→- Line 285: `test-provable verification (derived tier = test-provable):`\n    35→- Line 291: subagent prompt says `test-provable tier`\n    36→- Line 296-305: build, test, lint, coverage, grep-based AC checks — no Docker\n    37→- Line 331: `No Docker involved at any point.`\n    38→- 3/3 unit tests pass for AC2 group\n    39→\n    40→### AC3: runtime-provable dispatches build+run subagent, no Docker\n    41→**Result:** PASS\n    42→\n    43→**Evidence:**\n    44→- Line 333: `runtime-provable verification (derived tier = runtime-provable):`\n    45→- Line 339: subagent prompt says `runtime-provable tier`\n    46→- Lines 346-350: detects stack and run command (npm start, cargo run, python -m app)\n    47→- Lines 351-356: starts app, interacts with it, checks behavior\n    48→- Line 357: `Kill the running application process`\n    49→- Line 362: `Do NOT use Docker. Do NOT run codeharness stack start.`\n    50→- 4/4 unit tests pass for AC3 group\n    51→\n    52→### AC4: environment-provable dispatches full Docker flow\n    53→**Result:** PASS\n    54→\n    55→**Evidence:**\n    56→- Line 402: `environment-provable verification (derived tier = environment-provable): Full Docker container with no source code access.`\n    57→- Lines 403+: existing Docker flow (3d-i through 3d-viii) preserved unchanged\n    58→- 2/2 unit tests pass for AC4 group\n    59→\n    60→### AC5: escalate dispatches mixed-tier with [ESCALATE] marks\n    61→**Result:** PASS\n    62→\n    63→**Evidence:**\n    64→- Line 386: `escalate verification (derived tier = escalate):`\n    65→- Line 388: `at least one AC requires human judgment or external services. Use mixed-tier dispatch`\n    66→- Line 392: `escalate-tier ACs: mark each as [ESCALATE] in the proof document`\n    67→- Line 393: `All other ACs: dispatch verification at their individual tier level`\n    68→- Line 398: `If all non-escalated ACs pass: mark story done with escalation notes`\n    69→- 4/4 unit tests pass for AC5 group\n    70→\n    71→### AC6: Old story-level tags ignored, backward compat via AC parsing\n    72→**Result:** PASS\n    73→\n    74→**Evidence:**\n    75→- Line 273: `Ignore the story-level <!-- verification-tier: ... --> tag (if present). It is NOT used for dispatch.`\n    76→- No binary check for `<!-- verification-tier: unit-testable -->` exists in Step 3d-0\n    77→- Line 275 maps legacy AC tags so old stories still work\n    78→- 2/2 unit tests pass for AC6 group\n    79→\n    80→### AC7: LEGACY_TIER_MAP maps old tags to new tiers in Step 3d-0"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c452ddd6-f9a0-4cb1-9871-4264c6441698","uuid":"1d37ef0a-f737-4dc8-a646-de295644b45b","timestamp":"2026-03-27T12:27:43.292Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/verification/16-5-rewrite-harness-run-verification-dispatch-proof.md","content":"# Verification Proof: 16-5-rewrite-harness-run-verification-dispatch\n\n**Tier:** test-provable\n**Story:** 16-5-rewrite-harness-run-verification-dispatch\n**Date:** 2026-03-27\n**Verifier:** Claude Opus 4.6 (1M context)\n\n## Build & Test Results\n\n| Check | Result | Details |\n|-------|--------|---------|\n| Build (`npm run build`) | PASS | tsup compiled successfully, 0 errors |\n| BATS Tests (`npm test`) | PASS | 321 total, 316 passed, 5 failed (unrelated `all_tasks_complete` tests) |\n| Unit Tests (`vitest run`) | PASS | 34/34 dispatch-specific tests passed |\n| Lint (`npm run lint`) | PASS | 0 errors, 47 warnings (none in story-related files) |\n| Coverage (`vitest --coverage`) | PASS | 97.45% statements overall, 97.46% in verify module |\n\n## Acceptance Criteria Verification\n\n### AC1: Step 3d-0 derives tier from AC-level tags using maxTier()\n**Result:** PASS\n\n**Evidence:**\n- Line 269: `Step 3d-0: Read the story file and derive the verification tier from AC-level tags.`\n- Line 273: `Ignore the story-level <!-- verification-tier: ... --> tag (if present). It is NOT used for dispatch. AC-level tags are the sole source of truth.`\n- Line 275: `Parse ALL lines in the Acceptance Criteria section. For each AC, extract its <!-- verification: {tier} --> tag`\n- Line 277: `Compute the story's derived tier: maxTier(collectedTiers). If no AC-level tags are found at all, default to test-provable.`\n- 4/4 unit tests pass for AC1 group\n\n### AC2: test-provable dispatches build+test subagent, no Docker\n**Result:** PASS\n\n**Evidence:**\n- Line 285: `test-provable verification (derived tier = test-provable):`\n- Line 291: subagent prompt says `test-provable tier`\n- Line 296-305: build, test, lint, coverage, grep-based AC checks — no Docker\n- Line 331: `No Docker involved at any point.`\n- 3/3 unit tests pass for AC2 group\n\n### AC3: runtime-provable dispatches build+run subagent, no Docker\n**Result:** PASS\n\n**Evidence:**\n- Line 333: `runtime-provable verification (derived tier = runtime-provable):`\n- Line 339: subagent prompt says `runtime-provable tier`\n- Lines 346-350: detects stack and run command (npm start, cargo run, python -m app)\n- Lines 351-356: starts app, interacts with it, checks behavior\n- Line 357: `Kill the running application process`\n- Line 362: `Do NOT use Docker. Do NOT run codeharness stack start.`\n- 4/4 unit tests pass for AC3 group\n\n### AC4: environment-provable dispatches full Docker flow\n**Result:** PASS\n\n**Evidence:**\n- Line 402: `environment-provable verification (derived tier = environment-provable): Full Docker container with no source code access.`\n- Lines 403+: existing Docker flow (3d-i through 3d-viii) preserved unchanged\n- 2/2 unit tests pass for AC4 group\n\n### AC5: escalate dispatches mixed-tier with [ESCALATE] marks\n**Result:** PASS\n\n**Evidence:**\n- Line 386: `escalate verification (derived tier = escalate):`\n- Line 388: `at least one AC requires human judgment or external services. Use mixed-tier dispatch`\n- Line 392: `escalate-tier ACs: mark each as [ESCALATE] in the proof document`\n- Line 393: `All other ACs: dispatch verification at their individual tier level`\n- Line 398: `If all non-escalated ACs pass: mark story done with escalation notes`\n- 4/4 unit tests pass for AC5 group\n\n### AC6: Old story-level tags ignored, backward compat via AC parsing\n**Result:** PASS\n\n**Evidence:**\n- Line 273: `Ignore the story-level <!-- verification-tier: ... --> tag (if present). It is NOT used for dispatch.`\n- No binary check for `<!-- verification-tier: unit-testable -->` exists in Step 3d-0\n- Line 275 maps legacy AC tags so old stories still work\n- 2/2 unit tests pass for AC6 group\n\n### AC7: LEGACY_TIER_MAP maps old tags to new tiers in Step 3d-0","numLines":80,"startLine":1,"totalLines":127}}}
