{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01173TH1peaiZfceFvRWDn61","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Story 16.5: Rewrite harness-run Verification Dispatch\n     2→<!-- verification-tier: test-provable -->\n     3→\n     4→Status: verifying\n     5→\n     6→<!-- Note: Validation is optional. Run validate-create-story for quality check before dev-story. -->\n     7→\n     8→## Story\n     9→\n    10→As a codeharness developer,\n    11→I want the harness-run Step 3d verification dispatch to use four-tier routing instead of binary unit-testable/black-box,\n    12→So that each verification tier gets the appropriate verification strategy (build+test, local run, Docker stack, or escalation).\n    13→\n    14→## Acceptance Criteria\n    15→\n    16→- [ ] AC1: Given harness-run Step 3d-0, when a story file is read, then the verification tier is derived by parsing ALL AC-level `<!-- verification: {tier} -->` tags and computing `maxTier()` across them — the story-level `<!-- verification-tier: -->` tag is NOT used for dispatch <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n    17→- [ ] AC2: Given a story where all ACs are tagged `test-provable`, when Step 3d dispatches, then verification runs via a single subagent that builds, runs tests, and inspects code — no Docker, no running the app <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n    18→- [ ] AC3: Given a story where the derived tier is `runtime-provable`, when Step 3d dispatches, then a subagent builds the artifact, runs it locally (e.g., `npm start`, `cargo run`), interacts with it, and checks behavior — no Docker stack needed <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n    19→- [ ] AC4: Given a story where the derived tier is `environment-provable`, when Step 3d dispatches, then the existing full Docker verification flow runs (`codeharness stack start`, docker exec, observability checks) <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n    20→- [ ] AC5: Given a story where the derived tier is `escalate`, when Step 3d dispatches, then escalated ACs are marked `[ESCALATE]` and non-escalated ACs are verified at their individual tier levels <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n    21→- [ ] AC6: Given a story file with the old `<!-- verification-tier: unit-testable -->` story-level tag, when Step 3d reads it, then the story-level tag is ignored and AC-level tier derivation is used instead (backward compat: old stories still work because their AC tags are parsed) <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n    22→- [ ] AC7: Given Step 3d-0 encounters ACs with legacy tags like `<!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->` or `<!-- verification: integration-required -->`, when tier derivation runs, then `LEGACY_TIER_MAP` maps them to new tiers before computing `maxTier()` <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n    23→\n    24→## Tasks / Subtasks\n    25→\n    26→- [x] Task 1: Rewrite Step 3d-0 in `commands/harness-run.md` (AC: 1, 6, 7)\n    27→  - [x] 1.1: Replace the binary `<!-- verification-tier: unit-testable -->` tag check (L261-L267) with AC-level tier derivation instructions\n    28→  - [x] 1.2: Add instructions: parse all AC lines for `<!-- verification: {tier} -->` tags, map legacy values via `LEGACY_TIER_MAP`, compute `maxTier()`. Default to `test-provable` if no tags found\n    29→  - [x] 1.3: Add note: the story-level `<!-- verification-tier: -->` tag is ignored; AC-level tags are the source of truth\n    30→- [x] Task 2: Rewrite the test-provable dispatch section (AC: 2)\n    31→  - [x] 2.1: Keep the existing unit-testable subagent prompt (L272-L302) largely as-is — this IS the test-provable path. Update the heading/label from \"Unit-testable verification\" to \"test-provable verification\"\n    32→  - [x] 2.2: Update the subagent prompt to reference \"test-provable tier\" instead of \"unit-testable tier\"\n    33→- [x] Task 3: Add runtime-provable dispatch section (AC: 3)\n    34→  - [x] 3.1: Add a new subagent prompt block for `runtime-provable`. Build the project, then run it. Try `getRunCommand()` from StackProvider if available; otherwise fall back to common commands (`npm start`, `cargo run`, `python -m app`)\n    35→  - [x] 3.2: Subagent instructions: start the app, interact (CLI flags, HTTP to localhost), check output/behavior, kill process, generate proof document\n    36→  - [x] 3.3: No Docker stack. No `codeharness stack start`. The app runs locally.\n    37→- [x] Task 4: Keep environment-provable dispatch section (AC: 4)\n    38→  - [x] 4.1: Relabel the existing \"Black-box verification (default, no tag)\" section as \"environment-provable verification\"\n    39→  - [x] 4.2: No behavioral changes — the Docker flow (3d-i through 3d-viii) stays as-is\n    40→- [x] Task 5: Add escalate dispatch section (AC: 5)\n    41→  - [x] 5.1: Add a new section for `escalate` tier. For each AC in the story, check individual AC tier. Mark `escalate`-tier ACs as `[ESCALATE]`. For non-escalated ACs, dispatch verification at their individual tier level\n    42→  - [x] 5.2: If all non-escalated ACs pass, story is done with escalation notes\n    43→- [x] Task 6: Update Step 3a create-story prompt reference (AC: 1)\n    44→  - [x] 6.1: In Step 3a (L152-L170), update the AC tagging instruction from `cli-verifiable`/`integration-required` to the four new tier names with decision criteria. (Note: this is Task 6 in the tech spec but is scoped to this story because the dispatch depends on correctly tagged ACs)\n    45→\n    46→## Dev Notes\n    47→\n    48→This story modifies a single file: `commands/harness-run.md`. It's a prompt-engineering rewrite — no TypeScript code changes, no test changes, no build changes.\n    49→\n    50→### Key Constraints\n    51→\n    52→- **Single file change:** Only `commands/harness-run.md` is modified. The TypeScript utilities (`maxTier()`, `LEGACY_TIER_MAP`, `classifyTier()`, `parseVerificationTag()`) were built in stories 16-1 through 16-4 and are already available in `src/modules/verify/`.\n    53→- **The test-provable path already exists** as the \"Unit-testable verification\" block (L268-L307). Rename and minor wording updates only — do not rewrite the subagent prompt from scratch.\n    54→- **The environment-provable path already exists** as the \"Black-box verification\" block (L309+). Relabel only — do not change the Docker workflow.\n    55→- **runtime-provable is genuinely new.** The subagent prompt must be written from scratch. It builds the artifact, runs it locally, interacts with it, checks behavior, then kills the process. No Docker.\n    56→- **StackProvider does NOT have `getRunCommand()` yet.** The tech spec notes this as an optional method to add later. For now, the runtime-provable subagent prompt should try common run commands based on detected stack: `npm start` (Node.js), `cargo run` (Rust), `python -m app` (Python).\n    57→- **Step 3a update is in scope.** The create-story prompt in Step 3a currently tells agents to tag ACs with `cli-verifiable`/`integration-required`. Update it to use the four new tier names with a clear decision tree and examples. This ensures new stories get correct tier tags that the new dispatch can route on.\n    58→- **NFR: 300-line file limit does not apply** to `commands/harness-run.md` — it's a command prompt file, not a TypeScript module.\n    59→\n    60→### Backward Compatibility\n    61→\n    62→- Stories with old `<!-- verification-tier: unit-testable -->` still work: the story-level tag is ignored, but their AC-level tags (`cli-verifiable`/`integration-required`) are parsed and mapped via `LEGACY_TIER_MAP`.\n    63→- Stories with old AC tags (`cli-verifiable`, `integration-required`) are mapped: `cli-verifiable` -> `test-provable`, `integration-required` -> `environment-provable`. See `src/modules/verify/types.ts` L33-38.\n    64→- If a story has NO AC-level verification tags at all, default tier is `test-provable` (safest default — build and test only).\n    65→\n    66→### Current harness-run.md Structure (relevant sections)\n    67→\n    68→- **L152-L170 (Step 3a):** Create-story subagent prompt. Currently instructs tagging with `cli-verifiable`/`integration-required`. Needs update to four tiers.\n    69→- **L257-L267 (Step 3d-0):** Binary check for `<!-- verification-tier: unit-testable -->`. Needs rewrite to AC-level tier derivation.\n    70→- **L268-L307 (Unit-testable verification):** Subagent prompt for build+test+code-inspection. Becomes `test-provable` path. Minor wording updates.\n    71→- **L309+ (Black-box verification):** Full Docker flow. Becomes `environment-provable` path. Relabel only.\n    72→\n    73→### Files from previous stories that this story depends on\n    74→\n    75→- `src/modules/verify/types.ts` — `VerificationTier`, `TIER_HIERARCHY`, `maxTier()`, `LEGACY_TIER_MAP` (story 16-1)\n    76→- `src/modules/verify/parser.ts` — `classifyTier()`, `parseVerificationTag()` with backward compat (story 16-2)\n    77→- `src/modules/verify/proof.ts` — recognizes all four tier names in `**Tier:**` parsing (story 16-3)\n    78→- `src/modules/verify/validation-acs.ts` — `getTestProvableACs()`, `getEnvironmentProvableACs()` (story 16-4)\n    79→\n    80→### Project Structure Notes\n    81→\n    82→- `commands/harness-run.md` is a Claude Code slash command file (prompt, not code)\n    83→- Changes are to prompt text, not executable TypeScript\n    84→- The harness-run command orchestrates the full sprint loop — Step 3d is the verification dispatch within it\n    85→\n    86→### References\n    87→\n    88→- [Source: _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/tech-spec-verification-tier-rework.md#Task 5] — \"Rewrite harness-run verification dispatch (Step 3d)\"\n    89→- [Source: _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/tech-spec-verification-tier-rework.md#Task 6] — \"Update create-story prompt with tier criteria\"\n    90→- [Source: src/modules/verify/types.ts#L14-L38] — `VerificationTier`, `TIER_HIERARCHY`, `maxTier()`, `LEGACY_TIER_MAP`\n    91→- [Source: commands/harness-run.md#L257-L309] — Current Step 3d binary dispatch (to be rewritten)\n    92→- [Source: commands/harness-run.md#L152-L170] — Current Step 3a create-story prompt (to be updated)\n    93→\n    94→<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-START:story-verification -->\n    95→## Verification Requirements\n    96→\n    97→- [ ] Showboat proof document created (verification/16-5-rewrite-harness-run-verification-dispatch-proof.md)\n    98→- [ ] All acceptance criteria verified with real-world evidence via docker exec\n    99→- [ ] Test coverage meets target (100%)\n   100→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01M5ggaWpBnpHGzCP9ij59UW","session_id":"c452ddd6-f9a0-4cb1-9871-4264c6441698","uuid":"db5ed86f-150d-4661-a78c-d79533a61124","timestamp":"2026-03-27T12:31:06.972Z"}
