{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_015uGcod7R637wvLmdt1uTQf","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Story 16-6: Update create-story Prompt with Tier Criteria\n     2→<!-- verification-tier: test-provable -->\n     3→\n     4→## Status: backlog\n     5→\n     6→## Story\n     7→\n     8→As a codeharness developer,\n     9→I want the create-story prompt in harness-run Step 3a to include explicit tier decision criteria and examples,\n    10→So that the agent tags each AC with the correct `VerificationTier` consistently instead of guessing.\n    11→\n    12→## Acceptance Criteria\n    13→\n    14→- [ ] AC1: Given harness-run Step 3a prompt, when inspected, then it contains a decision tree with four tiers: `test-provable`, `runtime-provable`, `environment-provable`, `escalate` <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n    15→- [ ] AC2: Given the decision tree, when inspected, then it includes at least 4 concrete AC examples (one per tier) showing the Given/When/Then and which tier to assign <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n    16→- [ ] AC3: Given the Step 3a prompt, when inspected, then the tag format instruction reads `<!-- verification: {tier} -->` with `{tier}` being one of the four new tier names <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n    17→- [ ] AC4: Given the Step 3a prompt, when inspected, then it no longer references `cli-verifiable` or `integration-required` as valid tier names for NEW stories (old tags are only for backward compat in parsing) <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n    18→- [ ] AC5: Given the decision tree, when inspected, then `test-provable` criteria include: code structure, types, file existence, test passing, documentation, config changes, refactoring <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n    19→- [ ] AC6: Given the decision tree, when inspected, then `runtime-provable` criteria include: running the built application, CLI output, API endpoint behavior, exit codes <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n    20→- [ ] AC7: Given the decision tree, when inspected, then `environment-provable` criteria include: Docker, databases, observability stack, multiple services, distributed systems <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n    21→- [ ] AC8: Given the decision tree, when inspected, then `escalate` criteria include: physical hardware, human visual judgment, paid external services, GPU <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n    22→\n    23→## Technical Notes\n    24→\n    25→**File:** `commands/harness-run.md`\n    26→\n    27→**Step 3a prompt (L157-L172):** Replace the current AC tagging instruction:\n    28→\n    29→Current (L158):\n    30→```\n    31→For each AC, append `<!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->` or `<!-- verification: integration-required -->` based on whether the AC can be verified by running CLI commands in a subprocess. ACs referencing workflows, sprint planning, user sessions, or external system interactions should be tagged as integration-required.\n    32→```\n    33→\n    34→Replace with the decision tree from the tech spec:\n    35→\n    36→```\n    37→For each AC, determine the verification tier and append the tag:\n    38→\n    39→Is this AC about code structure, types, file existence, test passing, config, refactoring, or documentation?\n    40→-> test-provable\n    41→\n    42→Does this AC require running the built application and checking its output/behavior (CLI commands, API endpoints, exit codes)?\n    43→-> runtime-provable\n    44→\n    45→Does this AC require Docker, databases, observability stack, message queues, or multiple services running together?\n    46→-> environment-provable\n    47→\n    48→Does this AC require physical hardware, human visual judgment, GPU rendering, or paid external services?\n    49→-> escalate\n    50→\n    51→Tag format: <!-- verification: {tier} -->\n    52→\n    53→EXAMPLES:\n    54→- 'Given function X exists, when called with Y, then returns Z' -> test-provable (unit test proves it)\n    55→- 'Given the CLI is run with --flag, when output is checked, then it shows X' -> runtime-provable (need to run the binary)\n    56→- 'Given the server is running, when POST /api/users is called, then logs appear in VictoriaLogs' -> environment-provable (needs observability stack)\n    57→- 'Given the game renders at 60fps on a 4K display' -> escalate (needs GPU hardware)\n    58→```\n    59→\n    60→## Files to Change\n    61→\n    62→- `commands/harness-run.md` — Replace AC tagging instruction in Step 3a prompt (around L158) with four-tier decision tree and examples.\n    63→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01A9fh47XuAwURdEKBbEBJQa","session_id":"c452ddd6-f9a0-4cb1-9871-4264c6441698","uuid":"95bcda9f-b5c6-4e8c-b601-639e9c409378","timestamp":"2026-03-27T12:34:01.156Z"}
