{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01VCTnAwQgh9VcysMLgrXPnV","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→---\n     2→stepsCompleted: ['step-01-validate-prerequisites', 'step-02-design-epics', 'step-03-create-stories']\n     3→inputDocuments:\n     4→  - prd-overhaul.md\n     5→  - architecture-overhaul.md\n     6→  - ux-design-specification.md (v2)\n     7→---\n     8→\n     9→# codeharness Architecture Overhaul - Epic Breakdown\n    10→\n    11→## Overview\n    12→\n    13→This document provides the complete epic and story breakdown for the codeharness architecture overhaul, decomposing 40 FRs, 25 NFRs, and additional architecture/UX requirements into implementable stories.\n    14→\n    15→## Requirements Inventory\n    16→\n    17→### Functional Requirements\n    18→\n    19→FR1: Operator can initialize codeharness on any project type with a single command\n    20→FR2: System can detect and reuse a shared observability stack without port conflicts\n    21→FR3: Operator can configure OpenSearch as the observability backend via --opensearch-url\n    22→FR4: System can install BMAD non-interactively without prompting\n    23→FR5: System can clean up stale Docker verification containers before new runs\n    24→FR6: Operator can initialize a project without Docker when using remote endpoints\n    25→FR7: System can select next actionable story across all epics based on priority tiers\n    26→FR8: System maintains a single unified state file for story status, attempts, errors, blocked reasons\n    27→FR9: System can run autonomously for 8+ hours without crashes or unrecoverable state\n    28→FR10: System tracks attempt counts that persist across ralph and harness-run sessions\n    29→FR11: System can skip retry-exhausted stories and continue to next\n    30→FR12: System captures useful output from every iteration, including failed/timed-out ones\n    31→FR13: System can spawn a black-box verifier session in isolated Docker container\n    32→FR14: Verifier can run CLI commands via docker exec and capture output as proof\n    33→FR15: Verifier can query observability endpoints (VictoriaMetrics or OpenSearch) for evidence\n    34→FR16: Verifier can use agent-browser for web UI verification with screenshots\n    35→FR17: System can detect [FAIL] verdicts in proof documents outside code blocks\n    36→FR18: System can detect [ESCALATE] verdicts and count them separately\n    37→FR19: Verification adapts approach based on project type — never refuses any category\n    38→FR20: Verifier session has --allowedTools configured\n    39→FR21: System can orchestrate code review via BMAD code-review workflow\n    40→FR22: System can detect when review returns story to in-progress and re-trigger dev\n    41→FR23: Review module can fail independently without crashing sprint execution\n    42→FR24: System can orchestrate story implementation via BMAD dev-story workflow\n    43→FR25: System can detect when verification finds code bugs and return story to dev\n    44→FR26: Dev module can fail independently without crashing sprint execution\n    45→FR27: Operator can view complete results with a single codeharness status command in <10s\n    46→FR28: Status report shows done/failed/blocked/in-progress with per-story detail\n    47→FR29: Each failed story includes story ID, AC number, command, output, suggested fix\n    48→FR30: Operator can drill into specific story with codeharness status --story <id>\n    49→FR31: System reports cost, duration, and iteration count for each run\n    50→FR32: System can query OpenSearch for logs, metrics, and traces\n    51→FR33: System applies BMAD workflow patches encoding real verification requirements\n    52→FR34: Patches stored as editable markdown, not hardcoded strings\n    53→FR35: Each module has its own patches directory with role-specific enforcement\n    54→FR36: Patches include architectural context explaining WHY\n    55→FR37: Each module can fail gracefully without crashing other modules\n    56→FR38: Each module exposes a typed interface\n    57→FR39: Each module owns its own state\n    58→FR40: CLI commands are thin wrappers (<100 lines) calling module functions\n    59→\n    60→### NonFunctional Requirements\n    61→\n    62→NFR1: No module failure crashes the overall system — structured error results\n    63→NFR2: codeharness run survives 8+ hours without crashes or memory leaks\n    64→NFR3: Every ralph iteration produces a report, even on timeout — zero 0-byte outputs\n    65→NFR4: State files use atomic write (temp + rename)\n    66→NFR5: No set -e in bash scripts\n    67→NFR6: codeharness init completes in <5 minutes\n    68→NFR7: codeharness status returns in <3 seconds\n    69→NFR8: Story verification completes within 30 minutes\n    70→NFR9: Status report human-readable in <60 seconds\n    71→NFR10: State migration from old format is automatic and backwards-compatible\n    72→NFR11: Shared stack survives project-level init/teardown without data loss\n    73→NFR12: Docker port conflicts detected before starting containers\n    74→NFR13: Stale verification containers cleaned up automatically\n    75→NFR14: 100% test coverage on new/changed code\n    76→NFR15: Each module independently testable with mocked dependencies\n    77→NFR16: Integration tests cover full init→run→verify→status cycle\n    78→NFR17: Self-validation: codeharness run against own repo as CI gate\n    79→NFR18: No source file exceeds 300 lines\n    80→NFR19: Module interfaces documented with TypeScript types — no any\n    81→NFR20: Patches are markdown files readable by humans and agents\n    82→NFR21: All Docker images use pinned versions\n    83→NFR22: CLI interface unchanged\n    84→NFR23: Existing proofs remain valid\n    85→NFR24: Ralph integration continues to work\n    86→NFR25: Plugin commands and hooks unchanged\n    87→\n    88→### Additional Requirements\n    89→\n    90→- Result<T> type pattern for all module functions (Architecture Decision 1)\n    91→- Unified sprint-state.json replacing 5 scattered files (Architecture Decision 2)\n    92→- Module interface contracts with typed exports (Architecture Decision 3)\n    93→- ObservabilityBackend interface with Victoria/OpenSearch implementations (Architecture Decision 4)\n    94→- Status file protocol — ralph writes via jq, status reads directly (Architecture Decision 5)\n    95→- Phased migration — verify first, then sprint, infra, review, dev (Architecture Decision 6)\n    96→- codeharness status one-screen format (UX)\n    97→- codeharness status --story drill-down (UX)\n    98→- codeharness run --live rolling status (UX)\n    99→- Error capture on timeout with partial proof + git diff (UX)\n   100→- Agent-browser screenshot evidence in proofs (UX)\n   101→- OpenSearch query evidence in proofs (UX)\n   102→\n   103→### FR Coverage Map\n   104→\n   105→FR1: Epic 6 — Init any project type\n   106→FR2: Epic 6 — Shared stack detection\n   107→FR3: Epic 7 — OpenSearch backend\n   108→FR4: Epic 6 — BMAD non-interactive\n   109→FR5: Epic 6 — Stale container cleanup\n   110→FR6: Epic 6 — Init without Docker\n   111→FR7: Epic 2 — Cross-epic story selection\n   112→FR8: Epic 2 — Unified state file\n   113→FR9: Epic 3 — 8+ hour autonomous operation\n   114→FR10: Epic 2 — Persistent attempt counts\n   115→FR11: Epic 2 — Skip retry-exhausted stories\n   116→FR12: Epic 3 — Error capture on timeout\n   117→FR13: Epic 4 — Black-box verifier session\n   118→FR14: Epic 4 — Docker exec proof evidence\n   119→FR15: Epic 7 — Observability query (Victoria/OpenSearch)\n   120→FR16: Epic 8 — Agent-browser verification\n   121→FR17: Epic 4 — FAIL verdict detection\n   122→FR18: Epic 4 — ESCALATE verdict detection\n   123→FR19: Epic 4 — Project-agnostic verification\n   124→FR20: Epic 4 — Verifier --allowedTools\n   125→FR21: Epic 5 — Code review orchestration\n   126→FR22: Epic 5 — Review→dev re-trigger\n   127→FR23: Epic 5 — Review module failure independence\n   128→FR24: Epic 3 — Dev story orchestration\n   129→FR25: Epic 3 — Verify→dev feedback loop\n   130→FR26: Epic 3 — Dev module failure independence\n   131→FR27: Epic 2 — Status command <10s\n   132→FR28: Epic 2 — Status done/failed/blocked/in-progress\n   133→FR29: Epic 2 — Failed story detail (AC, command, output, fix)\n   134→FR30: Epic 2 — Status --story drill-down\n   135→FR31: Epic 2 — Cost/duration/iteration reporting\n   136→FR32: Epic 7 — OpenSearch log/metric/trace queries\n   137→FR33: Epic 9 — BMAD patches from operational failures\n   138→FR34: Epic 9 — Markdown patches, not hardcoded\n   139→FR35: Epic 9 — Per-module patches directory\n   140→FR36: Epic 9 — Patches include WHY context\n   141→FR37: Epic 1 — Module graceful failure\n   142→FR38: Epic 1 — Typed module interfaces\n   143→FR39: Epic 1 — Module-owned state\n   144→FR40: Epic 1 — Thin CLI commands\n   145→\n   146→## Epic List\n   147→\n   148→### Epic 1: Foundation — Result Types & Module Skeleton\n   149→Codebase has clean module boundaries with Result<T> pattern. Every function returns predictable success/failure. Module skeleton exists with typed interfaces and index.ts re-exports.\n   150→**FRs covered:** FR37, FR38, FR39, FR40\n   151→\n   152→### Epic 2: Unified State & Status Command\n   153→Operator runs `codeharness status` and sees full sprint state in one screen. Single source of truth for all story data. Story drill-down with AC-level detail.\n   154→**FRs covered:** FR7, FR8, FR10, FR11, FR27, FR28, FR29, FR30, FR31\n   155→\n   156→### Epic 3: Stable Sprint Execution\n   157→System runs 8+ hours unattended. Every iteration produces output. Failures captured with context. Timeouts save partial work. Dev and verify modules fail gracefully.\n   158→**FRs covered:** FR9, FR12, FR24, FR25, FR26\n   159→\n   160→### Epic 4: Verification Module\n   161→Black-box verification is reliable. No permission hangs, no 0-byte outputs. Proper FAIL/ESCALATE detection. Project-agnostic — never refuses any project type.\n   162→**FRs covered:** FR13, FR14, FR17, FR18, FR19, FR20\n   163→\n   164→### Epic 5: Code Review Module\n   165→Code review orchestration isolated in its own module. Review failures don't crash sprint. Review→dev loop works reliably.\n   166→**FRs covered:** FR21, FR22, FR23\n   167→\n   168→### Epic 6: Infrastructure Module\n   169→`codeharness init` is clean (<50 line command). Shared stack managed properly. Stale containers cleaned up. Port conflicts detected before failure. BMAD non-interactive.\n   170→**FRs covered:** FR1, FR2, FR4, FR5, FR6\n   171→\n   172→### Epic 7: OpenSearch Backend\n   173→Operator can use OpenSearch for observability. ObservabilityBackend interface with Victoria and OpenSearch implementations. No Docker needed for remote observability.\n   174→**FRs covered:** FR3, FR15, FR32\n   175→\n   176→### Epic 8: Agent-Browser Verification\n   177→Web projects get real browser verification. Navigate pages, interact with elements, capture annotated screenshots as proof evidence.\n   178→**FRs covered:** FR16\n   179→\n   180→### Epic 9: Enforcement & Patches\n   181→BMAD workflow patches encode real operational learnings per module role. Patches stored as markdown, loaded at runtime, include architectural context.\n   182→**FRs covered:** FR33, FR34, FR35, FR36\n   183→\n   184→### Epic 10: Self-Validation & Adaptation\n   185→Comprehensive validation AC suite covering all harness functionality. The harness validates itself, fixes what fails using its own dev→review→verify cycle, and produces a clean validation report. When this passes, v1.0 ships.\n   186→**FRs covered:** Meta — validates all 40 FRs + NFRs + UX + regression ACs from 62 action items\n   187→\n   188→## Epic 1: Foundation — Result Types & Module Skeleton\n   189→\n   190→Establish the module architecture pattern: Result<T> type, module skeleton with index.ts re-exports, shared types, thin command wrappers.\n   191→\n   192→### Story 1.1: Result Type & Shared Types\n   193→\n   194→As a developer, I want a consistent Result<T> type used by all module functions, So that error handling is predictable and no module crash kills the system.\n   195→\n   196→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   197→\n   198→1. **Given** `src/types/result.ts` exists, **When** imported, **Then** it exports `Result<T>`, `ok(data)`, and `fail(error, context?)`.\n   199→2. **Given** `ok(data)` is called, **When** checked, **Then** `result.success === true` and `result.data` contains the value.\n   200→3. **Given** `fail(error)` is called, **When** checked, **Then** `result.success === false` and `result.error` contains the message.\n   201→4. **Given** `src/types/state.ts` exists, **When** imported, **Then** it exports `SprintState` interface matching architecture decision.\n   202→5. **Given** `src/types/observability.ts` exists, **When** imported, **Then** it exports `ObservabilityBackend` interface with `queryLogs`, `queryMetrics`, `queryTraces`, `healthCheck`.\n   203→6. **Given** `src/types/index.ts` exists, **When** imported, **Then** it re-exports all shared types.\n   204→\n   205→### Story 1.2: Module Skeleton & Index Pattern\n   206→\n   207→As a developer, I want module directories with index.ts re-exports for all 5 modules, So that module boundaries are enforced and imports follow the index-only pattern.\n   208→\n   209→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   210→\n   211→1. **Given** `src/modules/{infra,sprint,verify,dev,review}/index.ts` exist, **When** imported, **Then** each exports typed function stubs returning `Result<T>`.\n   212→2. **Given** all stubs, **When** called, **Then** each returns `fail('not implemented')`.\n   213→3. **Given** CLI commands, **When** reviewed, **Then** no command file exceeds 100 lines.\n   214→4. **Given** module imports, **When** reviewed, **Then** no module imports from another module's internal files.\n   215→\n   216→### Story 1.3: Migrate Existing Tests to Module Structure\n   217→\n   218→As a developer, I want existing tests reorganized into module `__tests__/` directories, So that each module is independently testable.\n   219→\n   220→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   221→\n   222→1. **Given** existing tests in `src/lib/__tests__/`, **When** migrated, **Then** verify-related tests move to `src/modules/verify/__tests__/`.\n   223→2. **Given** the migration, **When** all tests run, **Then** all pass with no regressions.\n   224→3. **Given** the migration, **When** coverage measured, **Then** overall coverage does not decrease.\n   225→\n   226→## Epic 2: Unified State & Status Command\n   227→\n   228→Single source of truth for sprint state. `codeharness status` shows everything in one screen.\n   229→\n   230→### Story 2.1: Sprint State Module — Unified State File\n   231→\n   232→As an operator, I want a single `sprint-state.json` replacing all scattered state files, So that all story state is in one place.\n   233→\n   234→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   235→\n   236→1. **Given** `src/modules/sprint/state.ts` exists, **When** `getSprintState()` called, **Then** returns `Result<SprintState>`.\n   237→2. **Given** old format files exist, **When** first access, **Then** auto-migrates to sprint-state.json.\n   238→3. **Given** `updateStoryStatus()` called, **When** writing, **Then** uses atomic write (temp + rename).\n   239→4. **Given** sprint-state.json, **When** read, **Then** parse time <100ms.\n   240→\n   241→### Story 2.2: Story Selection — Cross-Epic Prioritization\n   242→\n   243→As a system, I want story selection that prioritizes by readiness across all epics, So that actionable stories are processed first.\n   244→\n   245→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   246→\n   247→1. **Given** `getNextStory()` called, **Then** returns stories in priority: proof-exists > in-progress > verifying > backlog.\n   248→2. **Given** story with attempts >= 10, **When** selected, **Then** skipped with reason \"retry-exhausted\".\n   249→3. **Given** no actionable stories, **When** called, **Then** returns `ok(null)`.\n   250→\n   251→### Story 2.3: Status Report — One Screen Overview\n   252→\n   253→As an operator, I want `codeharness status` to show full state in one screen, So that I understand what happened in 10 seconds.\n   254→\n   255→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   256→\n   257→1. **Given** active run, **When** `codeharness status` called, **Then** shows: current story, phase, AC progress, iteration, cost, elapsed.\n   258→2. **Given** completed run, **When** called, **Then** shows: completed, failed (with error), blocked, skipped.\n   259→3. **Given** failed story in summary, **Then** shows: story key, AC number, one-line error.\n   260→4. **Given** status called, **When** measured, **Then** returns in <3 seconds.\n   261→5. **Given** action items in state, **When** called, **Then** shows with NEW/CARRIED labels.\n   262→\n   263→### Story 2.4: Status Story Drill-Down\n   264→\n   265→As an operator, I want `codeharness status --story <id>` for AC-level detail, So that I can see exactly what failed.\n   266→\n   267→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   268→\n   269→1. **Given** story with failures, **When** drill-down called, **Then** shows each AC with PASS/FAIL/ESCALATE.\n   270→2. **Given** FAIL verdict, **Then** shows: command, expected, actual, reason, suggested fix.\n   271→3. **Given** attempt history, **Then** shows each attempt's outcome.\n   272→4. **Given** proof exists, **Then** shows proof path and AC counts.\n   273→\n   274→## Epic 3: Stable Sprint Execution\n   275→\n   276→System runs 8+ hours unattended. Every iteration produces output.\n   277→\n   278→### Story 3.1: Error Capture on Timeout\n   279→\n   280→As an operator, I want every iteration to produce a report even on timeout, So that work is never silently lost.\n   281→\n   282→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   283→\n   284→1. **Given** timeout (exit 124), **When** detected, **Then** captures: git diff, state delta, partial stderr.\n   285→2. **Given** captured data, **When** saved, **Then** written to iteration timeout report with story key and duration.\n   286→3. **Given** any iteration, **When** completes, **Then** report file exists with non-zero content.\n   287→\n   288→### Story 3.2: Graceful Dev Module\n   289→\n   290→As a system, I want dev module to return Result<T> and never crash the sprint, So that one story's failure doesn't halt the run.\n   291→\n   292→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   293→\n   294→1. **Given** `developStory(key)` called, **Then** invokes BMAD dev-story and returns `Result<DevResult>`.\n   295→2. **Given** dev workflow fails, **Then** returns `fail(error)` — never throws.\n   296→3. **Given** dev workflow times out, **Then** preserves partial work and returns error.\n   297→\n   298→### Story 3.3: Verify→Dev Feedback Loop\n   299→\n   300→As a system, I want verification failures to return stories to dev with findings, So that the dev module can fix exact issues.\n   301→\n   302→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   303→\n   304→1. **Given** failing ACs found, **When** processed, **Then** story status → `in-progress` with failing AC details.\n   305→2. **Given** story returned to dev, **When** dev runs, **Then** prompt includes failing ACs and output.\n   306→3. **Given** N >= 10 cycles, **When** reached, **Then** story marked `blocked`.\n   307→4. **Given** attempt count, **Then** persists in sprint-state.json across sessions.\n   308→\n   309→### Story 3.4: 8-Hour Stability Test\n   310→\n   311→As an operator, I want verified 8-hour unattended operation, So that I can trust overnight runs.\n   312→\n   313→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   314→\n   315→1. **Given** 8-hour run against test fixture, **Then** no crashes, no memory leaks, no unrecoverable state.\n   316→2. **Given** mixed success/failure/timeout iterations, **Then** sprint-state.json consistent and status accurate.\n   317→3. **Given** Docker killed mid-verification, **Then** logged and next story attempted.\n   318→\n   319→## Epic 4: Verification Module\n   320→\n   321→Extract and stabilize black-box verification.\n   322→\n   323→### Story 4.1: Verify Module Extraction\n   324→\n   325→As a developer, I want verify code extracted into `src/modules/verify/`, So that verification is self-contained.\n   326→\n   327→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   328→\n   329→1. **Given** migration to `src/modules/verify/`, **Then** all existing tests pass.\n   330→2. **Given** `verifyStory(key)` called, **Then** returns `Result<VerifyResult>` with AC-level results.\n   331→3. **Given** `parseProof(path)` called, **Then** returns `Result<ProofQuality>` with FAIL/ESCALATE detection.\n   332→4. **Given** module boundary, **Then** imports only from `verify/index.ts`.\n   333→\n   334→### Story 4.2: Project-Agnostic Verification\n   335→\n   336→As a developer, I want verification to never refuse a project type, So that all projects get verified.\n   337→\n   338→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   339→\n   340→1. **Given** CLI project, **Then** uses docker exec + stdout capture.\n   341→2. **Given** Claude plugin, **Then** uses `docker exec ... claude --print`.\n   342→3. **Given** any project, **Then** no AC tagged `integration-required` unless genuinely needs external systems.\n   343→\n   344→### Story 4.3: Verifier Session Reliability\n   345→\n   346→As a system, I want verifier sessions to never hang or produce 0 bytes, So that every attempt produces output.\n   347→\n   348→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   349→\n   350→1. **Given** verifier spawns `claude --print`, **Then** includes `--allowedTools`.\n   351→2. **Given** nested claude inside Docker, **Then** also includes `--allowedTools`.\n   352→3. **Given** verifier times out, **Then** partial proof saved and error returned.\n   353→4. **Given** stale containers, **Then** cleaned up before new verification.\n   354→\n   355→## Epic 5: Code Review Module\n   356→\n   357→### Story 5.1: Review Module Extraction\n   358→\n   359→As a developer, I want code review extracted into `src/modules/review/`, So that review is isolated.\n   360→\n   361→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   362→\n   363→1. **Given** `reviewStory(key)` called, **Then** returns `Result<ReviewResult>`.\n   364→2. **Given** review fails, **Then** returns Result with error — never throws.\n   365→3. **Given** review returns to in-progress, **Then** triggers dev with findings.\n   366→4. **Given** module boundary, **Then** imports only from `review/index.ts`.\n   367→\n   368→## Epic 6: Infrastructure Module\n   369→\n   370→### Story 6.1: Infra Module — Init Extraction\n   371→\n   372→As a developer, I want init.ts split into infra module components, So that no file exceeds 300 lines.\n   373→\n   374→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   375→\n   376→1. **Given** extraction, **Then** `src/commands/init.ts` is <100 lines.\n   377→2. **Given** `infra.initProject(opts)` called, **Then** handles: stack detection, deps, Docker, BMAD, state, docs.\n   378→3. **Given** no file in `src/modules/infra/` exceeds 300 lines.\n   379→4. **Given** existing init tests, **Then** all pass after migration.\n   380→\n   381→### Story 6.2: Shared Stack Management\n   382→\n   383→As an operator, I want shared stack properly managed, So that init works cleanly across projects.\n   384→\n   385→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   386→\n   387→1. **Given** shared stack running, **When** init runs, **Then** detects and reuses.\n   388→2. **Given** port conflict, **When** detected, **Then** reports before starting containers.\n   389→3. **Given** stale containers, **When** cleanup runs, **Then** removed.\n   390→4. **Given** `status --check-docker`, **Then** reports correct shared container names.\n   391→\n   392→### Story 6.3: Non-Interactive BMAD Install\n   393→\n   394→As an operator, I want BMAD to install without prompts, So that init works headless.\n   395→\n   396→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   397→\n   398→1. **Given** BMAD not installed, **When** init runs, **Then** `npx bmad-method install --yes --tools claude-code`.\n   399→2. **Given** BMAD installed, **When** init runs, **Then** skips install, applies patches.\n   400→3. **Given** install fails, **Then** meaningful error with command and output.\n   401→\n   402→## Epic 7: OpenSearch Backend\n   403→\n   404→### Story 7.1: ObservabilityBackend Interface & Victoria Implementation\n   405→\n   406→As a developer, I want the backend interface with Victoria as default, So that existing behavior is preserved.\n   407→\n   408→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   409→\n   410→1. **Given** no OpenSearch config, **When** `getObservabilityBackend()` called, **Then** returns `VictoriaBackend`.\n   411→2. **Given** Victoria backend, **When** query methods called, **Then** query existing Victoria endpoints.\n   412→3. **Given** Victoria backend, **When** `healthCheck()` called, **Then** checks all services running.\n   413→\n   414→### Story 7.2: OpenSearch Implementation\n   415→\n   416→As an operator, I want `--opensearch-url` to configure OpenSearch backend, So that I can use remote observability.\n   417→\n   418→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   419→\n   420→1. **Given** `--opensearch-url` passed, **When** init completes, **Then** state records `opensearch` backend.\n   421→2. **Given** OpenSearch backend, **When** `queryLogs()` called, **Then** queries OpenSearch `_search` API.\n   422→3. **Given** OpenSearch backend, **When** `healthCheck()` called, **Then** checks cluster health.\n   423→4. **Given** OpenSearch configured, **When** verifier runs, **Then** proof shows OpenSearch queries.\n   424→5. **Given** OpenSearch configured, **When** init runs, **Then** no local Docker stack started.\n   425→\n   426→## Epic 8: Agent-Browser Verification\n   427→\n   428→### Story 8.1: Agent-Browser Integration\n   429→\n   430→As a web developer, I want verification to use agent-browser for UI testing, So that web features are verified with real browser interaction.\n   431→\n   432→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   433→\n   434→1. **Given** `verify/browser.ts` exists, **When** AC references UI elements, **Then** uses agent-browser via docker exec.\n   435→2. **Given** screenshots captured, **Then** saved to `verification/screenshots/` and referenced in proof.\n   436→3. **Given** before/after screenshots, **Then** visual diff evidence available.\n   437→4. **Given** Dockerfile.verify updated, **Then** agent-browser installed in container.\n   438→\n   439→## Epic 9: Enforcement & Patches\n   440→\n   441→### Story 9.1: Per-Module Patches Directory\n   442→\n   443→As a developer, I want patches organized by module role, So that enforcement rules connect to responsibilities.\n   444→\n   445→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   446→\n   447→1. **Given** `patches/{dev,review,verify,sprint,retro}/` exist, **Then** patch templates load from role directory.\n   448→2. **Given** patches are markdown, **Then** no rebuild required to update.\n   449→3. **Given** each patch, **Then** includes WHY section with architectural reasoning.\n   450→4. **Given** patch application, **Then** reads from `patches/{role}/` not hardcoded strings.\n   451→\n   452→## Epic 10: Self-Validation & Adaptation\n   453→\n   454→### Story 10.1: Validation AC Suite\n   455→\n   456→As a release manager, I want comprehensive validation ACs covering all harness functionality, So that self-validation tests every capability.\n   457→\n   458→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   459→\n   460→1. **Given** suite generated, **Then** includes one AC per FR (40 ACs).\n   461→2. **Given** suite generated, **Then** includes key NFR ACs (8h stability, status <3s, atomic writes, <300 line files).\n   462→3. **Given** suite generated, **Then** includes UX ACs (status format, error detail, live mode).\n   463→4. **Given** existing 32 verifying stories, **Then** their ACs imported as regression tests.\n   464→5. **Given** 62 action items, **Then** resolved items become regression ACs.\n   465→\n   466→### Story 10.2: Validation Infrastructure\n   467→\n   468→As a release manager, I want the harness to fix what validation finds, So that it adapts using its own pipeline.\n   469→\n   470→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   471→\n   472→1. **Given** validation sprint created, **Then** contains all validation ACs as stories.\n   473→2. **Given** validation AC fails, **Then** harness creates fix story → dev → review → verify.\n   474→3. **Given** fix applied, **Then** only failing AC re-validated (not entire suite).\n   475→4. **Given** AC fails after 10 attempts, **Then** marked as specific blocker.\n   476→\n   477→### Story 10.3: Self-Validation Run\n   478→\n   479→As a release manager, I want `codeharness validate` to produce a clean report, So that v1.0 release gate is met.\n   480→\n   481→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   482→\n   483→1. **Given** `codeharness validate` run, **Then** report shows: total ACs, passed, failed, blocked, adaptation cycles.\n   484→2. **Given** all pass, **Then** outputs \"RELEASE GATE: PASS — v1.0 ready\".\n   485→3. **Given** some fail, **Then** each failure has: AC description, command, output, attempts, blocker.\n   486→4. **Given** validation run, **Then** `codeharness status` shows progress in real time.\n   487→5. **Given** CI mode, **Then** `codeharness validate --ci` returns exit 0 on pass, 1 on fail.\n   488→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01A9fh47XuAwURdEKBbEBJQa","session_id":"c452ddd6-f9a0-4cb1-9871-4264c6441698","uuid":"1d044bad-0f14-436d-a67b-1bf82b23f2e6","timestamp":"2026-03-27T12:34:01.564Z"}
