{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01QLMSc2g2PupxZgvNxSBHqF","type":"tool_result","content":"   128→- [ ] Task 6: Update create-story prompt with tier criteria\n   129→  - File: `commands/harness-run.md` (Step 3a)\n   130→  - Action: Replace the current vague AC tagging instruction with explicit decision tree:\n   131→    ```\n   132→    For each AC, determine the verification tier:\n   133→\n   134→    Is this AC about code structure, types, file existence, test passing, or documentation?\n   135→    → test-provable\n   136→\n   137→    Does this AC require running the built application and checking its output/behavior?\n   138→    → runtime-provable\n   139→\n   140→    Does this AC require Docker, databases, observability stack, or multiple services?\n   141→    → environment-provable\n   142→\n   143→    Does this AC require physical hardware, human visual judgment, or paid external services?\n   144→    → escalate\n   145→\n   146→    Tag: <!-- verification: {tier} -->\n   147→\n   148→    EXAMPLES:\n   149→    - \"Given function X exists, when called with Y, then returns Z\" → test-provable (unit test proves it)\n   150→    - \"Given the CLI is run with --flag, when output is checked, then it shows X\" → runtime-provable (need to run the binary)\n   151→    - \"Given the server is running, when POST /api/users is called, then logs appear in VictoriaLogs\" → environment-provable (needs observability stack)\n   152→    - \"Given the game renders at 60fps on a 4K display\" → escalate (needs GPU hardware)\n   153→    ```\n   154→\n   155→- [ ] Task 7: Update knowledge and enforcement docs\n   156→  - Files: `knowledge/verification-patterns.md`, `patches/dev/enforcement.md`, `patches/review/enforcement.md`, `patches/verify/story-verification.md`\n   157→  - Action: Replace all old tier terminology with new. Add tier decision guide to knowledge file."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01A9fh47XuAwURdEKBbEBJQa","session_id":"c452ddd