{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01CPTdjgPxEDb3zWX5wiD9NG","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Story 16-6: Update create-story Workflow with Tier Criteria\n     2→<!-- verification-tier: test-provable -->\n     3→\n     4→## Status: ready-for-dev\n     5→\n     6→<!-- Note: Validation is optional. Run validate-create-story for quality check before dev-story. -->\n     7→\n     8→## Story\n     9→\n    10→As a codeharness developer,\n    11→I want the create-story BMAD workflow to embed the four-tier verification decision tree directly in its instructions and quality checklist,\n    12→So that ACs get correct `<!-- verification: {tier} -->` tags whether create-story is invoked from harness-run or directly via `/create-story`.\n    13→\n    14→## Acceptance Criteria\n    15→\n    16→- [ ] AC1: Given `_bmad/bmm/workflows/4-implementation/create-story/instructions.xml` Step 5 (AC quality gate), when inspected, then it contains a verification tier tagging instruction with the four tiers: `test-provable`, `runtime-provable`, `environment-provable`, `escalate` <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n    17→- [ ] AC2: Given the tier tagging instruction in `instructions.xml`, when inspected, then it includes a decision tree with criteria for each tier and at least 4 concrete AC examples (one per tier) <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n    18→- [ ] AC3: Given the tier tagging instruction in `instructions.xml`, when inspected, then the tag format reads `<!-- verification: {tier} -->` with `{tier}` being one of the four new tier names <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n    19→- [ ] AC4: Given `instructions.xml`, when inspected, then it does NOT reference `cli-verifiable` or `integration-required` as valid tier names for new stories <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n    20→- [ ] AC5: Given `_bmad/bmm/workflows/4-implementation/create-story/checklist.md`, when inspected, then the Spec Coverage DISASTERS section (3.6) includes a check for missing or incorrect `<!-- verification: {tier} -->` tags on ACs <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n    21→- [ ] AC6: Given `instructions.xml` Step 5 tier decision tree, when inspected, then `test-provable` criteria include: code structure, types, file existence, test passing, documentation, config changes, refactoring <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n    22→- [ ] AC7: Given `instructions.xml` Step 5 tier decision tree, when inspected, then `runtime-provable` criteria include: running the built application, CLI output, API endpoint behavior, exit codes <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n    23→- [ ] AC8: Given `instructions.xml` Step 5 tier decision tree, when inspected, then `environment-provable` criteria include: Docker, databases, observability stack, multiple services, distributed systems <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n    24→- [ ] AC9: Given `instructions.xml` Step 5 tier decision tree, when inspected, then `escalate` criteria include: physical hardware, human visual judgment, paid external services, GPU <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n    25→- [ ] AC10: Given `commands/harness-run.md` Step 3a, when inspected, then it already contains the four-tier decision tree (completed by story 16-5 — this AC is a regression check only) <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n    26→\n    27→## Tasks / Subtasks\n    28→\n    29→- [ ] Task 1: Update `instructions.xml` Step 5 AC quality gate with tier tagging (AC: 1, 2, 3, 4, 6, 7, 8, 9)\n    30→  - [ ] 1.1: In Step 5 (`<step n=\"5\">`), after the existing AC quality check `<action>` block (lines 288-298), add a new `<action>` block titled \"VERIFICATION TIER TAGGING\" that contains the four-tier decision tree\n    31→  - [ ] 1.2: The decision tree must list criteria for each tier: `test-provable` (code structure, types, file existence, tests, docs, config, refactoring), `runtime-provable` (running app, CLI output, API endpoints, exit codes), `environment-provable` (Docker, databases, observability, multi-service), `escalate` (physical hardware, human visual judgment, paid services, GPU)\n    32→  - [ ] 1.3: Include 4 concrete examples, one per tier, in Given/When/Then format showing which tier to assign\n    33→  - [ ] 1.4: Specify the tag format: `<!-- verification: {tier} -->`\n    34→  - [ ] 1.5: Add instruction: \"Default to `test-provable` when unsure\"\n    35→  - [ ] 1.6: Ensure NO references to old `cli-verifiable` or `integration-required` tier names exist anywhere in `instructions.xml`\n    36→- [ ] Task 2: Update `checklist.md` Spec Coverage DISASTERS section (AC: 5)\n    37→  - [ ] 2.1: In Section 3.6 (Spec Coverage DISASTERS), add a new bullet for missing or incorrect verification tier tags: \"**Missing verification tier tags:** Every AC must have a `<!-- verification: {tier} -->` tag appended. Check that each AC has one, and that the tier assignment follows the decision tree criteria.\"\n    38→- [ ] Task 3: Verify harness-run Step 3a regression (AC: 10)\n    39→  - [ ] 3.1: Read `commands/harness-run.md` Step 3a and confirm the four-tier decision tree is present (done by story 16-5). No changes needed — this is a read-only check.\n    40→\n    41→## Dev Notes\n    42→\n    43→This story modifies two BMAD workflow files and performs one regression check. No TypeScript code changes, no test changes, no build changes.\n    44→\n    45→### Key Constraints\n    46→\n    47→- **Two files to edit:** `_bmad/bmm/workflows/4-implementation/create-story/instructions.xml` and `_bmad/bmm/workflows/4-implementation/create-story/checklist.md`. Both are prompt/workflow files, not executable code.\n    48→- **harness-run Step 3a already done:** Story 16-5 updated `commands/harness-run.md` Step 3a with the four-tier decision tree and examples. AC10 is a regression check only — do NOT re-edit harness-run.md.\n    49→- **The create-story workflow has NO tier tagging today.** The `instructions.xml` Step 5 has an AC quality gate (lines 288-298) that checks AC quality but says nothing about appending verification tier tags. When create-story is invoked directly (not via harness-run), ACs get no tier tags at all. This story fixes that gap.\n    50→- **NFR: 300-line file limit does not apply** to workflow XML and checklist markdown files.\n    51→\n    52→### Context from Previous Stories\n    53→\n    54→- Story 16-1 defined `VerificationTier` type with four tiers in `src/modules/verify/types.ts`\n    55→- Story 16-2 rewrote parser to use `classifyTier()` with keyword matching\n    56→- Story 16-3 updated proof validation to recognize all four tier names\n    57→- Story 16-4 updated validation ACs and runner for tier dispatch\n    58→- Story 16-5 rewrote harness-run Step 3d (verification dispatch) AND Step 3a (create-story prompt in harness-run)\n    59→\n    60→### The Gap This Story Fills\n    61→\n    62→When `/create-story` is invoked directly (not through harness-run), the agent follows `instructions.xml` — which currently has no mention of verification tiers. The harness-run Step 3a prompt passes tier criteria through the Agent tool prompt, but that only works when create-story is called as a subagent of harness-run. This story embeds the tier criteria into the create-story workflow itself so it works both ways.\n    63→\n    64→### Project Structure Notes\n    65→\n    66→- `_bmad/bmm/workflows/4-implementation/create-story/instructions.xml` — Main workflow instructions (XML format)\n    67→- `_bmad/bmm/workflows/4-implementation/create-story/checklist.md` — Quality validation checklist\n    68→- `_bmad/bmm/workflows/4-implementation/create-story/template.md` — Story template (no changes needed)\n    69→- `_bmad/bmm/workflows/4-implementation/create-story/workflow.yaml` — Workflow config (no changes needed)\n    70→\n    71→### References\n    72→\n    73→- [Source: _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/tech-spec-verification-tier-rework.md#Task 6] — \"Update create-story prompt with tier criteria\"\n    74→- [Source: _bmad/bmm/workflows/4-implementation/create-story/instructions.xml#Step 5] — Current AC quality gate (lines 286-298)\n    75→- [Source: _bmad/bmm/workflows/4-implementation/create-story/checklist.md#Section 3.6] — Spec Coverage DISASTERS section\n    76→- [Source: commands/harness-run.md#L158-L164] — Step 3a four-tier decision tree (already completed by 16-5)\n    77→- [Source: src/modules/verify/types.ts#L14-L38] — `VerificationTier`, `TIER_HIERARCHY`, `LEGACY_TIER_MAP`\n    78→\n    79→<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-START:story-verification -->\n    80→## Verification Requirements\n    81→\n    82→- [ ] Showboat proof document created (verification/16-6-update-create-story-tier-criteria-proof.md)\n    83→- [ ] All acceptance criteria verified with real-world evidence via docker exec\n    84→- [ ] Test coverage meets target (100%)\n    85→\n    86→## Documentation Requirements\n    87→\n    88→- [ ] Relevant AGENTS.md files updated\n    89→- [ ] Exec-plan created in docs/exec-plans/active/16-6-update-create-story-tier-criteria.md\n    90→\n    91→## Testing Requirements\n    92→\n    93→- [ ] Unit tests written for all new/changed code\n    94→- [ ] Coverage target: 100%\n    95→<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-END:story-verification -->\n    96→\n    97→## Dev Agent Record\n    98→\n    99→### Agent Model Used\n   100→\n   101→Claude Opus 4.6 (1M context)\n   102→\n   103→### Debug Log References\n   104→\n   105→### Completion Notes List\n   106→\n   107→### File List\n   108→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_017LihutVV2SfFnAxcKajyK2","session_id":"c452ddd6-f9a0-4cb1-9871-4264c6441698","uuid":"34d90ad6-fed0-416e-8290-afd8c5309fe3","timestamp":"2026-03-27T12:38:54.434Z"}
