{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_0124dyQMyxZpMDabwyRiHTdY","type":"tool_result","content":"44-     ```\n45-     [INFO] Skipping {story_key}: retry-exhausted ({count}/{max_attempts})\n46-     ```\n47:   - **Blocked (escalated):** A `verifying` story that already has a proof document (`verification/{story_key}-proof.md` exists) with `escalated > 0` and `pending === 0` is blocked. Increment `stories_skipped`, append `{story_key}: blocked (escalated ACs)` to `skipped_reasons`, and print:\n48-     ```\n49:     [INFO] Skipping {story_key}: blocked (escalated ACs)\n50-     ```\n51-\n52:3. **Prioritize remaining stories.** Sort actionable stories into priority tiers (process highest tier first, file order within each tier):\n53-   - **Tier A — Proof exists, needs validation:** Status is `verifying` AND `verification/{story_key}-proof.md` exists (but story is not blocked per step 2). These are quick wins — just need validation.\n54-   - **Tier B — In-progress or review:** Status is `in-progress` or `review`. Resume partially-completed work.\n55-   - **Tier C — Verifying without proof:** Status is `verifying` AND no proof document exists. Needs full Docker verification.\n--\n63-\n64-7. Print the plan:\n65-   ```\n66:   [INFO] Next story: {story_key} (status: {current_status}, tier: {A|B|C|D})\n67-   [INFO] Parent epic: Epic {N}\n68-   [INFO] Stories in epic: {done_count}/{total_count} done\n69-   ```\n--\n155-\n156-```\n157-Use the Agent tool with:\n158:  prompt: \"Run /create-story for story {story_key}. The sprint-status.yaml is at _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/sprint-status.yaml. Auto-discover the next backlog story and create it. For each AC, append a verification tier tag using this decision tree:\n159-\n160:**Tier Decision Tree (append one `<!-- verification: {tier} -->` tag per AC):**\n161:- `test-provable` — AC can be verified by building the project and running tests/linters/grep. No running app needed. Examples: 'function X exists', 'type Y is exported', 'test Z passes', 'file has <300 lines'.\n162:- `runtime-provable` — AC requires running the app locally and checking its behavior (CLI output, HTTP response, process lifecycle). No Docker stack needed. Examples: 'CLI prints usage when invoked with --help', 'server responds 200 on /health', 'process exits 0 on valid input'.\n163:- `environment-provable` — AC requires a full environment (Docker stack, database, observability, multi-service interaction). Examples: 'logs appear in VictoriaLogs', 'metrics are emitted to VictoriaMetrics', 'container communicates with service X'.\n164:- `escalate` — AC genuinely cannot be automated (requires physical hardware, paid external service, human visual judgment). This is rare. Examples: 'UI looks correct on mobile', 'payment processes successfully in production'.\n165-\n166:Default to `test-provable` when unsure. Do NOT ask the user any questions — proceed autonomously. Do NOT run git commit. Do NOT run git add. Do NOT modify sprint-status.yaml.\n167-\n168-MANDATORY — End your response with a `## Session Issues` section listing:\n169-- Problems encountered (errors, ambiguities in epic definition, missing context)\n--\n266-\n267-> **CRITICAL — DERIVE VERIFICATION TIER BEFORE DISPATCHING. DO NOT SKIP THIS STEP.**\n268-\n269:**Step 3d-0: Read the story file and derive the verification tier from AC-level tags.**\n270-\n271-Read `_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/{story_key}.md`.\n272-\n273:**Ignore the story-level `<!-- verification-tier: ... -->` tag** (if present). It is NOT used for dispatch. AC-level tags are the sole source of truth.\n274-\n275:Parse ALL lines in the Acceptance Criteria section. For each AC, extract its `<!-- verification: {tier} -->` tag (if present). Map any legacy tag values via `LEGACY_TIER_MAP`: `cli-verifiable` → `test-provable`, `integration-required` → `environment-provable`, `unit-testable` → `test-provable`, `black-box` → `environment-provable`. Collect all parsed tiers into an array.\n276-\n277:Compute the story's derived tier: `maxTier(collectedTiers)`. If no AC-level tags are found at all, default to `test-provable`.\n278-\n279:Dispatch based on the derived tier:\n280:- **`test-provable`** → Use **test-provable verification** (below). No Docker, no running the app.\n281:- **`runtime-provable`** → Use **runtime-provable verification** (below). Build and run the app locally — no Docker stack.\n282:- **`environment-provable`** → Use **environment-provable verification** (below). Full Docker flow.\n283:- **`escalate`** → Use **escalate verification** (below). Mixed-tier dispatch per AC.\n284-\n285:**test-provable verification (derived tier = test-provable):**\n286-\n287-Use a **single subagent** for the entire verification. This keeps build/test output out of the parent context (saves ~80% of verification tokens).\n288-\n289-```\n290-Use the Agent tool with:\n291:  prompt: \"Verify story {story_key} using local CLI checks (test-provable tier).\n292-\n293-Story file: _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/{story_key}.md\n294-\n--\n330-2. Parse the result: ALL_PASS → mark story `done`. PARTIAL → treat as failure (Step 3d-vii Path A).\n331-3. **No Docker involved at any point.** Skip steps 3d-i through 3d-viii entirely.\n332-\n333:**runtime-provable verification (derived tier = runtime-provable):**\n334-\n335-Use a **single subagent** for the entire verification. Build the project, then run it locally — no Docker stack needed.\n336-\n337-```\n338-Use the Agent tool with:\n339:  prompt: \"Verify story {story_key} using local runtime checks (runtime-provable tier).\n340-\n341-Story file: _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/{story_key}.md\n342-\n--\n383-2. Parse the result: ALL_PASS → mark story `done`. PARTIAL → treat as failure (Step 3d-vii Path A).\n384-3. **No Docker involved at any point.** Skip steps 3d-i through 3d-viii entirely.\n385-\n386:**escalate verification (derived tier = escalate):**\n387-\n388:When the derived tier is `escalate`, at least one AC requires human judgment or external services. Use mixed-tier dispatch:\n389-\n390:1. Re-read the story file. For each AC, extract its individual `<!-- verification: {tier} -->` tag (with legacy mapping as in Step 3d-0).\n391:2. Group ACs by their individual tier:\n392:   - `escalate`-tier ACs: mark each as `[ESCALATE]` in the proof document with the reason \"Requires human judgment or external service — cannot be automated.\"\n393:   - All other ACs: dispatch verification at their individual tier level. Use the corresponding subagent prompt (test-provable, runtime-provable, or environment-provable) to verify those ACs specifically.\n394-3. Generate proof document at `verification/{story_key}-proof.md`. Include:\n395:   - PASS/FAIL verdict for each non-escalated AC (with evidence)\n396:   - `[ESCALATE]` verdict for each escalated AC (with reason)\n397-4. Run `codeharness verify --story {story_key}` to validate the proof format.\n398:5. If all non-escalated ACs pass: mark story `done` with escalation notes. Print: `[WARN] Story {story_key} has {N} escalated ACs — marking done with known limitations`.\n399:6. If any non-escalated AC fails: treat as failure (Step 3d-vii Path A).\n400:7. If any non-escalated ACs were dispatched via the environment-provable path, run cleanup (step 3d-viii) to remove Docker containers and temp workspaces.\n401-\n402:**environment-provable verification (derived tier = environment-provable):** Full Docker container with no source code access.\n403-\n404-**No internal timeout.** Verification takes as long as it takes. Ralph's iteration timeout is the safety net.\n405-\n--\n513-\n514-where `passed` is ACs with PASS verdict and `total` is all ACs.\n515-\n516:- If `pending === 0` and `escalated === 0` → proof quality passed. Update sprint-status.yaml: change `{story_key}` status to `done`. Print: `[OK] Story {story_key}: verifying → done`. Proceed to cleanup (step 3d-viii).\n517:- If `escalated > 0` and `pending === 0` → verifier could not reach some ACs. **Before accepting escalation, diagnose WHY:**\n518-  1. Read the proof document. For each `[ESCALATE]` AC, check the reason.\n519-  2. **If the reason is infrastructure/tooling** (container missing binary, tree-shaking, Docker not configured, wrong version installed): this is NOT a valid escalation. The infrastructure needs fixing. Treat as **Path C** below.\n520:  3. **If the reason is genuinely impossible to automate** (requires physical hardware, paid external service, human visual judgment): accept the escalation. Print: `[WARN] Story {story_key} has {N} genuinely escalated ACs — marking done with known limitations`. Update status to `done`.\n521:  4. **Do NOT leave stories at `verifying` with escalated ACs.** Either fix the infra problem (Path C) or accept and mark done.\n522-- If `pending > 0` → proof has gaps. Treat as failure (step 3d-vii).\n523-\n524-If the verifier made code fixes (detected by checking `git diff` after verification), run:\n--\n807-   - Bugs discovered during implementation or verification\n808-   - Workarounds applied (tech debt introduced this session)\n809-   - Code quality concerns raised by reviewers\n810:   - Verification gaps (escalated ACs, weak evidence)\n811-   - Tooling/infrastructure problems (sandbox, permissions, CLI issues)\n812-3. **Cost analysis** — from the cost report:\n813-   - Total API-equivalent cost this sprint"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_017LihutVV2SfFnAxcKajyK2","session_id":"c452ddd6-f9a0-4cb1-9871-4264c6441698","uuid":"53dd00a4-8966-44d6-a6d7-bbfa8f26dc7f","timestamp":"2026-03-27T12:39:38.668Z"}
