{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01X5qFqHhP8DbsJBBLDke5tM","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01CHCZrJPpb4buXSVCrZ2Tb3","name":"Edit","input":{"replace_all":false,"file_path":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad/bmm/workflows/4-implementation/create-story/instructions.xml","old_string":"      4. Can each AC be verified by running the system and observing output (not just reading source code)?\n    </action>\n\n    <!-- Developer context section - MOST IMPORTANT PART -->","new_string":"      4. Can each AC be verified by running the system and observing output (not just reading source code)?\n    </action>\n\n    <!-- VERIFICATION TIER TAGGING — every AC must get a tier tag -->\n    <critical>🏷️ VERIFICATION TIER TAGGING — Append a tier tag to every AC</critical>\n    <action>For each AC in the story file, append a verification tier tag using the format:\n      `&lt;!-- verification: {tier} --&gt;`\n      where {tier} is one of: `test-provable`, `runtime-provable`, `environment-provable`, `escalate`.\n\n      **Tier Decision Tree — assign the LOWEST tier that can verify the AC:**\n\n      - `test-provable` — AC can be verified by building the project and running tests, linters, type checks, or grep.\n        No running application needed. Criteria: code structure, types, file existence, test passing,\n        documentation changes, config changes, refactoring, module exports, file line counts.\n      - `runtime-provable` — AC requires running the built application and checking its behavior.\n        No Docker stack needed. Criteria: CLI output, API endpoint behavior, exit codes, HTTP responses,\n        process lifecycle, server startup, command-line flags.\n      - `environment-provable` — AC requires a full environment (Docker stack, database, observability, multi-service).\n        Criteria: Docker containers, databases, observability stack (logs/metrics/traces), multiple services\n        communicating, distributed system behavior.\n      - `escalate` — AC genuinely cannot be automated. This is rare.\n        Criteria: physical hardware, human visual judgment, paid external services, GPU-dependent rendering.\n\n      **Concrete Examples (one per tier):**\n\n      - `test-provable`: Given the VerificationTier type in types.ts, when inspected, then it includes all four tier names\n        `&lt;!-- verification: test-provable --&gt;`\n      - `runtime-provable`: Given the CLI is invoked with `--help`, when the process runs, then it prints usage information and exits 0\n        `&lt;!-- verification: runtime-provable --&gt;`\n      - `environment-provable`: Given a request is sent to the API, when the observability stack is running, then the request appears in VictoriaLogs\n        `&lt;!-- verification: environment-provable --&gt;`\n      - `escalate`: Given the dashboard is rendered on a mobile device, when a human reviews it, then the layout is visually correct\n        `&lt;!-- verification: escalate --&gt;`\n\n      **Default to `test-provable` when unsure.**\n\n      Do NOT use legacy tier names (`cli-verifiable`, `integration-required`, `unit-testable`, `black-box`).\n      Only the four tiers above are valid for new stories.\n    </action>\n\n    <!-- Developer context section - MOST IMPORTANT PART -->"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1387,"cache_read_input_tokens":42774,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1387,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":3,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_017LihutVV2SfFnAxcKajyK2","session_id":"c452ddd6-f9a0-4cb1-9871-4264c6441698","uuid":"47ccba98-7aab-44ad-8792-e31fed61566b"}
