ST tier that can verify the AC:**\u001b[39m\n\u001b[31m+\u001b[39m\n\u001b[31m+       - `test-provable` — AC can be verified by building the project and running tests, linters, type checks, or grep.\u001b[39m\n\u001b[31m+         No running application needed. Criteria: code structure, types, file existence, test passing,\u001b[39m\n\u001b[31m+         documentation changes, config changes, refactoring, module exports, file line counts.\u001b[39m\n\u001b[31m+       - `runtime-provable` — AC requires running the built application and checking its behavior.\u001b[39m\n\u001b[31m+         No Docker stack needed. Criteria: CLI output, API endpoint behavior, exit codes, HTTP responses,\u001b[39m\n\u001b[31m+         process lifecycle, server startup, command-line flags.\u001b[39m\n\u001b[31m+       - `environment-provable` — AC requires a full environment (Docker stack, database, observability, multi-service).\u001b[39m\n\u001b[31m+         Criteria: Docker containers, databases, observability stack (logs/metrics/traces), multiple services\u001b[39m\n\u001b[31m+         communicating, distributed system behavior.\u001b[39m\n\u001b[31m+       - `escalate` — AC genuinely cannot be automated. This is rare.\u001b[39m\n\u001b[31m+         Criteria: physical hardware, human visual judgment, paid external services, GPU-dependent rendering.\u001b[39m\n\u001b[31m+\u001b[39m\n\u001b[31m+       **Concrete Examples (one per tier):**\u001b[39m\n\u001b[31m+\u001b[39m\n\u001b[31m+       - `test-provable`: Given the VerificationTier type in types.ts, when inspected, then it includes all four tier names\u001b[39m\n\u001b[31m+         `&lt;!-- verification: test-provable --&gt;`\u001b[39m\n\u001b[31m+       - `runtime-provable`: Given the CLI is invoked with `--help`, when the process runs, then it prints usage information and exits 0\u001b[39m\n\u001b[31m+         `&lt;!-- verification: runtime-provable --&gt;`\u001b[39m\n\u001b[31m+       - `environment-provable`: Given a request is sen