{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_018LADb7YCGnHQyD15Nanz5g","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Done. Here is the summary.\n\n## Code Review Summary\n\n**Story 16-6** modifies two BMAD workflow files (`instructions.xml`, `checklist.md`) and adds one content-verification test file. All 10 ACs are correctly implemented in the workflow files.\n\n### Issues Found and Fixed\n\n**HIGH-1: Silent false-pass on missing section markers** — All tests used `indexOf()` without checking for -1. If a marker string was removed, `slice(start, -1)` would silently search the wrong content and tests could false-pass. Fixed by adding `extractSection()` helper that throws on missing markers.\n\n**HIGH-2: Brittle section boundary in 15+ tests** — The `<!-- Developer context section` marker and `Concrete Examples` marker were used inline in every test. If either string changed, all tests would fail silently. Fixed by centralizing into `tierSection()` and `decisionTreeOnly()` helpers.\n\n**MEDIUM-1: Massive code duplication (AC6-AC9)** — 18 individual test cases each repeated the same 3-line section extraction. Refactored to use `it.each()` with the helper functions, reducing the file from 291 lines to 183 lines.\n\n**MEDIUM-2: AC4 test comment ambiguity** — The test comment said \"may appear in a 'do not use' warning\" but didn't explain why the boundary was chosen. Clarified the comment to explicitly document that old names in the warning section below the tree are expected.\n\n### Results\n\n- **Tests:** 151 files, 3958 tests, all passing\n- **Coverage:** 96.86% overall (target: 90%), all 158 files above 80% floor\n- **Story status:** Updated to `verifying`\n\n---\n\n## Session Issues\n\n**Bugs found:**\n- HIGH: Silent false-pass risk from unchecked `indexOf()` returns in test file (fixed)\n- HIGH: Brittle section boundary markers duplicated across 15+ test cases (fixed)\n- MEDIUM: Massive code duplication in AC6-AC9 tests (fixed)\n- MEDIUM: Ambiguous test comments on AC4 boundary choice (fixed)\n\n**Code quality issues NOT fixed (LOW):**\n- The `tierSection()` helper is called once per `it.each` iteration (up to 18 times). Could cache the result in a `describe`-level `let` with `beforeAll`, but overhead is negligible for file-read tests.\n- The test file reads workflow XML/markdown at file-system level. If the project restructures `_bmad/` paths, the relative `../../../../` paths will break. A project-level path constant would be better but is low priority.\n\n**Coverage gaps:**\n- None. All files above 80% floor, 96.86% overall.\n\n**Architecture concerns:**\n- None. This story only modifies prompt/workflow files and content-verification tests.\n\n**Items sent back for re-development:**\n- None.\n\n## Token Report\n\n- Total tool calls: 12\n- By tool: Bash: 3, Read: 5, Edit: 1, Grep: 3, Write: 1, other: 0 (note: 1 Read was the story file read at start)\n- Largest Bash outputs (top 3 by line count): `npx vitest run` (~40 lines), `codeharness coverage` (~4 lines), `git diff/status` (~12 lines)\n- Files read: 5 unique, 5 total reads (no file read 3+ times)\n- Redundant operations: None. The second read of the test file (before Write) was required by tool contract."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a8ee93dee82e97ea6 (use SendMessage with to: 'a8ee93dee82e97ea6' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 48960\ntool_uses: 14\nduration_ms: 155515</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c452ddd6-f9a0-4cb1-9871-4264c6441698","uuid":"9dc9d7a4-d05f-4684-907b-f688be2340c0","timestamp":"2026-03-27T12:47:12.746Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Run /bmad-code-review for the story at _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/16-6-update-create-story-tier-criteria.md — perform adversarial review, fix all HIGH and MEDIUM issues found. After fixing, run `npx vitest run` and ensure all tests pass. Run `codeharness coverage --min-file 80` and ensure all files pass the per-file 